  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (865bc46 2022-03-28T00:13:30.542149+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen using `import \"forge-std/console.sol\";` in a test file, the `console.log` statements seem to have an impact on `msg.sender`. Specifically, in certain (TBD) cases when the `console.log` statement is removed, the contract's `msg.sender` is changed from the test contract to `address(0)`\r\n\r\nReproduction coming soon, still boiling it down cause this doesn't always seem to happen...",
